// Reading, language & memory causal DAG — Byrne, MacDonald & Buckley (2002)
// cohort (study_id="rlm"). Down Syndrome Education International.
// PROPOSAL 2026-07-13 (Claude Code/Fable 5). See
// notes/202607131500-byrne-dag-proposal.md for the full construct crosswalk,
// the RLI-edge mapping, the readgrp / reading-matched selection caveat, the
// latent extensions and the lagged companion.
// Paste into https://www.dagitty.net/dags.html to render/inspect.
//
// This is the BYRNE analogue of the authoritative RLI base graph
// dag/dag-language-reading.dagitty (revised 2026-07-10). It keeps the RLI
// causal SKELETON among the skills that have a Byrne counterpart, DROPS the RLI
// nodes with no measure in the prepared extract, COLLAPSES the unmeasured code
// route into direct edges, and REPLACES the randomised intervention (IG/IS)
// with the observational cohort factor readgrp. Exposure/outcome roles are
// assigned per analysis; only GA is annotated latent (a structural property).
//
// CONTEMPORANEOUS (single-wave) structure, matching the RLI base graph. The
// study's founding reciprocal question (does reading feed language & memory?)
// is inherently longitudinal and belongs in a time-lagged companion — see the
// note (mirrors dag/dag-language-reading-lagged.dagitty for RLI).
//
// Node symbols = Byrne CSV columns (study-local, per datasets.py), with the RLI
// symbol they map to in [brackets]:
//   age     - Age in months                                        [A]
//   GA      - General Ability [latent]                             [GA]
//   readgrp - Reading group / cohort factor (1 Down syndrome,
//             2 average readers, 3 reading-matched) — OBSERVATIONAL,
//             non-manipulable; NOT the RLI randomised exposure      [replaces IG/IS]
//   bassim  - BAS similarities / verbal reasoning   (GA indicator) [new]
//   basmat  - BAS matrices / non-verbal reasoning   (GA indicator; wave 3+) [new]
//   basdig  - BAS recall of digits (verbal short-term / phon. memory) [RW]
//   bpvs    - British Picture Vocabulary Scale (receptive vocabulary)  [RV]
//   trog    - Test for Reception of Grammar (receptive grammar)        [RG]
//   basread - BAS word reading (primary outcome)                       [WR]
//   basspel - BAS spelling (outcome; involves writing letters)         [PS]
//   basnum  - BAS number skills (arithmetic outcome)              [new]
//   woco    - WORD reading comprehension (outcome)                [new; Simple View]
//   (speed  - processing speed, wave 3+ only, sparse — documented in the note,
//             deliberately kept OUT of the edge block)
//
// Adaptation summary (full table in the note):
//   * IG/IS  -> readgrp   (randomised cause replaced by an observational cohort
//                          marker; NO term here is a clean causal effect).
//   * DROP   HS EV LF EI EG SP LS PA NW TE TR  (no measure in the extract).
//   * COLLAPSE the code route (LS/PA/NW): basdig -> basread and bpvs -> basread
//                          now stand in for RLI's ...-> (code route) -> WR chain.
//   * ADD    woco, basnum, bassim, basmat, and the GA indicator structure.
//   * basread is NO LONGER a sink: woco (reading comprehension) sits downstream.
//
// Verified acyclic (12 nodes; roots age, GA, readgrp). The age <-> readgrp
// bidirected edge is a DESIGN-induced association (reading-matched children are
// younger by construction), not a causal arrow; it leaves the graph acyclic.

dag {
GA [latent]

// --- universal parents (as in RLI: age & GA into every observed node; here
//     readgrp too, as the cohort/population marker) ---
age     -> { bassim basmat basdig basnum bpvs trog basread basspel woco }
GA      -> { bassim basmat basdig basnum bpvs trog basread basspel woco }
readgrp -> { bassim basmat basdig basnum bpvs trog basread basspel woco }

// --- verbal short-term / phonological memory (RLI RW), code route collapsed ---
basdig -> { bpvs basread basspel basnum woco }

// --- receptive vocabulary (RLI RV) ---
bpvs -> { trog basread woco }

// --- receptive grammar (RLI RG) -> reading comprehension (Simple View) ---
trog -> woco

// --- word reading (RLI WR) -> reading comprehension (Simple View) ---
basread -> woco

// --- design-induced association (matching), NOT causal: reading-matched younger ---
age <-> readgrp
}
